{
  "texts": [
    "IoT technology also allows farmers to collect and analyze realtime data on various aspects of their fields (Sadiku et al. 2018).",
    "To efficiently allocate resources in smart agriculture, a Wireless Sensor Network (WSN) is essential.",
    "This network connects sensor nodes to enable seamless communication and improve networking throughput.",
    "Machine learning-based approaches, such as dynamic clustering with Back-Propagation Neural Network and Particle Swarm Optimization, are used to enhance energy-efficient networking for applications like intelligent irrigation and smart crop monitoring (Tyagi et al. 2020).",
    "IoT technology plays a crucial role in improving efficiency, reducing production costs, and ensuring sustainability in agriculture."
  ]
}